<dl id="s14024r"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us14" href="#s14024r">Oxen of the Sun: </a><a href="../../ff/unbs/s14all.htm#s14024r">sector 24(r)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> by chance medley</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> more dangerous is it to wit-wanton it with <font color="green">[jest at]</font> the majesty of God. Wherefore, if without thine invention, and against thy will, <mark>by chance medley</mark> thou hittest Scripture in ordinary discourse, yet fly to the city of refuge and pray to God to forgive thee. <small> William Peacock, <a name="WPEP" href="/udra/udex.htm#wpep"><cite title="source">English Prose from Mandeville to Ruskin</cite></a> (1903), 80, Fuller</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
